          "version": "7.7"
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "A wide cinematic shot pushes slowly through a dense misty forest at dusk as shafts of pale blue moonlight pierce the canopy and illuminate a cloaked figure kneeling beside a shallow stream, an older man with a long grey beard and weathered face, his gnarled hands hovering over the water's surface as faint golden runes flicker to life beneath his palms and ripple outward across the current, his heavy wool cloak shifting in a low wind as he speaks in a deep gravelly voice without looking up — \"The seal is weakening, I can feel it in the water, something old is pushing through and we are not ready\" — while the ambient soundscape layers the steady babble of the stream over stones, the creak and groan of ancient tree trunks swaying, a distant owl calling twice, and a low sub-harmonic drone pulsing beneath the earth like a buried heartbeat. | A medium tracking shot follows a young woman with short dark braided hair and pointed ears moving quickly through the same forest, leather armor creaking as she vaults over a moss-covered fallen log and lands in a crouch, twin daggers drawn and glinting in the fractured moonlight, her amber eyes scanning the treeline as her breath fogs in the cold air and she speaks in a sharp urgent whisper — \"I saw three of them crossing the ridge an hour ago, they're not scouting anymore, they're heading straight for the village and they don't care who sees them\" — while branches snap under her boots, wet leaves rustle as she moves through underbrush, a distant wolf howl echoes across the valley, and the low rhythmic pulse of war drums begins faintly from beyond the ridge. | A low-angle close-up frames a massive figure stepping out from behind a stone ruin, a towering orc warlord in blackened iron plate armor with a jagged scar running from his left brow to his jaw, yellowed tusks jutting from his lower lip as he plants a huge notched battle axe into the dirt and leans on it, firelight from a camp behind him casting dancing orange light across his scarred face and the tattered banner hanging from his pauldron, his voice a low rumbling growl — \"They sent their old man to read the water again, let him read, by the time he understands what's coming the gates will already be ash\" — while a campfire crackles and pops, armor clinks as soldiers shift in the background, a horse stamps and snorts nervously, and the war drums grow louder in a steady building cadence. | A medium shot frames a young boy no older than twelve standing on the stone battlements of a small torchlit village wall, his oversized leather helmet slipping down over his eyes as he pushes it back with one hand and peers out into the dark forest below, gripping a wooden practice sword in the other, torchlight flickering across his round face as the wind picks up and the banners on the wall snap taut, and he speaks in a trembling voice trying to sound brave — \"I can see the fires out there, past the river, there's a lot of them, but my father said the wall has never fallen and I believe him\" — while torch flames gutter and hiss in the wind, the village bell begins tolling slow and heavy in the distance, dogs bark from somewhere below, and the war drums from beyond the forest are now clearly audible as a steady rhythmic pound. | A tight close-up captures the elven woman bursting through the village gate and skidding to a halt in the muddy torchlit courtyard, breathless, as villagers scramble around her carrying bundles and herding children, her braids whipping as she turns to face a grey-haired woman in chainmail descending stone steps with a drawn longsword — the village captain, jaw set and eyes hard — and the elf speaks between heaving breaths, daggers still in hand — \"Maren, listen to me, the north pass is already gone, they flanked us through the gorge, if we don't collapse the bridge now there won't be a village to defend by sunrise\" — while panicked voices overlap in the courtyard, a blacksmith hammers frantically on steel, livestock brays and scatters, boots pound on cobblestone, and the war drums are now thunderous and close. | A wide dramatic crane shot rises above the village wall as Maren strides to the battlement edge beside the boy and the elf, her chainmail catching torchlight as she raises her longsword overhead and the villagers lining the wall lift their weapons in response — pitchforks, hammers, bows drawn taut — and she speaks in a commanding voice that carries over the drums and the wind and the chaos below, steady and absolute — \"Then we collapse the bridge, and we hold what's left, nobody leaves this wall, nobody falls alone, that is the only plan now\" — while the war drums reach a fever pitch, a war horn blasts long and deep from the treeline, arrows ignite along the wall in a cascade of flickering orange light, the crowd roars in defiant unison, and the low drone beneath the earth swells into a resonant harmonic that shakes dust from the stone."
      ],
